.TH DPI-PROBE 1 "June 2026" "dpi-probe 1.1.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
dpi-probe \- detect DPI interference and RST injection from your vantage point
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B dpi-probe
.I HOST
.RB [ \-p | \-\-port
.IR PORT ]
.RB [ \-\-sni
.IR NAME ]
.RB [ \-\-benign\-sni
.IR NAME ]
.RB [ \-\-deep ]
.RB [ \-\-timeout
.IR SECS ]
.RB [ \-\-json ]
.RB [ \-\-no\-color ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B dpi-probe
tells you whether a censoring network is actively interfering with a connection,
and how \(em from your side of the wall, without needing access to the server.
.PP
Its first tier is an SNI differential: two TLS handshakes to the same host, one
carrying a benign control SNI and one carrying the name you care about. If the
benign handshake completes but the target one is reset or silently dropped, the
block is keyed on the SNI \(em textbook deep packet inspection. If plain TCP
itself never completes, it is an IP or port block, not DPI.
.PP
With
.BR \-\-deep ,
a second tier inspects packets: a forged RST from a censorship middlebox almost
never matches the server's network distance, so its IP TTL betrays it.
.B dpi-probe
learns the server's true TTL from the genuine SYN-ACK and flags any RST whose
TTL implies a closer, forged origin. This tier needs
.BR scapy (1)
and root.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.I HOST
The target host: your proxy or server, or any host whose path you want to test.
.TP
.BI \-p ", " \-\-port " PORT"
Target port (default: 443).
.TP
.BI \-\-sni " NAME"
The SNI you actually care about \(em the one a censor might block. Defaults to
.IR HOST .
.TP
.BI \-\-benign\-sni " NAME"
The control SNI assumed not to be blocked (default:
.IR www.example.com ).
.TP
.B \-\-deep
Enable packet-level RST-injection forensics. Requires root and the
.B deep
extra
.RB ( "pip install 'dpi-probe[deep]'" ).
.TP
.BI \-\-timeout " SECS"
Per-probe timeout in seconds (default: 5).
.TP
.B \-\-json
Emit machine-readable JSON.
.TP
.B \-\-no\-color
Strip ANSI escapes.
.TP
.BR \-V ", " \-\-version
Print the version and exit.
.SH "VERDICTS"
.B clean
\(em no interference from here.
.B sni_blocked
\(em benign SNI works, target SNI reset or dropped.
.B rst_injected
\(em a forged RST caught by its TTL.
.B port_blocked
\(em TCP never completed.
.B tls_interference
\(em all TLS fails regardless of SNI.
.B inconclusive
\(em cause could not be isolated.
.SH "EXIT STATUS"
.TP
.B 0
Clean.
.TP
.B 1
Interference detected.
.TP
.B 2
Usage error.
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
Test a specific masquerade SNI with packet forensics:
.B sudo dpi-probe myproxy.example.net \-\-sni www.microsoft.com \-\-deep
.TP
Alert when an endpoint starts getting tampered with:
.B dpi-probe myproxy.example.net \-\-json | jq \-e '.verdict == "clean"'
.SH "SEE ALSO"
.BR scapy (1)
.PP
